green spot is a single pot still irish whiskey, produced specifically for mitchell & son of dublin, by irish distillers at the midleton distillery, cork, ireland. it is one of the few remaining bonded irish whiskeys, and along with yellow spot (see below) are currently the only brands specifically produced for and sold by an independent wine merchant in ireland. green spot was described by whiskey writer jim murray as "unquestionably one of the world's great whiskeys."